    {
      "note_no": "47",
      "note": "The participial noun mubtil is derived from the verb abt ala, \"he made a false [or \"vain\"] claim\", or \"tried to disprove the truth [of something]\", or \"to reduce [something] to nothing\", or \"to prove [it] to be of no account\", or \"null and 'void\", or \"unfounded\", \"false\", \"spurious\", etc.; irrespective of whether the object is true or false, authentic or spurious, valid or unfounded (Lisan al-'Arab and Taj al-'Arus)."
    }
